KW  - Commercial banking
KW  - Lines of credit
KW  - Market reaction
AB  - Prior research has shown, and this paper confirms, that when the market becomes aware a line of credit is granted, the borrower’s stock has a positive and significant reaction. The borrower’s reaction is used to identify the exact date the market becomes aware of the granting of the line of credit. This date is used as a one day window to investigate whether the bank’s stock also reacts. This reaction will be most obvious with large lines of credit. All lines of credit, larger than US$1 billion, granted during the years 1993–1996 are investigated. The results show, as predicted, a positive and significant reaction by the bank’s stock.
